'''''Even Heroes Need a Parachute''''' is the first [[studio album]] by [[United States|American]] [[Christian rock]] band [[This Beautiful Republic]]. It was released on [[April 3]], [[2007]] through [[ForeFront Records]].<ref name="billboard">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?JSESSIONID=Ln1kLT1Jjp8kny7jWgnpHlQpZB79Lm7FtPvs1vQF7bsqWQ3yFQKQ!-1825686150&pid=833307&aid=902871 |title=This Beautiful Republic <U+2013> Even Heroes Need a Parachute |work=[[Billboard]] |accessdate=2008-08-01}}</ref>

==Background==

==Style and songwriting==
[[Allmusic]] labeled ''Even Heroes Need a Parachute'''s genre as "[[Alternative CCM]]", comparing its sound to [[rock music|rock]] bands [[Jimmy Eat World]], [[Foo Fighters]], and [[Anberlin]].<ref name="allmusic">{{cite web |url=http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=10:apfpxzy5ld0e |title=Even Heroes Need a Parachute Review |publisher=[[Allmusic]] |accessdate=2008-08-01 |author=Jared Johnson}}</ref>

===Lyrical themes===
[[Lead singer]] Ben Olin said that the album's title was chosen to "emphasize the common ground that all humans share. No matter who you are or what you do, the need for a [[savior]] is vital. So we hope, beyond anything else, to show people this savior, [[Christ]], and to give listeners a brush with [[eternity]]."<ref name="cmt">{{cite web |url=http://www.christianitytoday.com/music/artists/thisbeautifulrepublic.html Christian Music Today |title=This Beautiful Republic |work=[[Christianity Today|Christian Music Today]] |accessdate=2008-08-01}}</ref>

==Singles==
The song "Black Box" was released as a single in mid 2007, becoming notably played on [[Christian rock]] radios in early September 2007.<ref name="ccmmag">{{cite web |url=http://www.ccmmagazine.com/music/artist/this_beautiful_republic/browseT/11554690/ |title=This Beautiful Republic Wins Fans Abroad |date=September 2007 |accessdate=2008-08-01 |work=[[CCM Magazine]]}}</ref>

